To autoload custom packages for your local file system you have to instruct composer to look in these folders as well, so instead of autoloading the modules folder you have to reference it as a repository.

In your `composer.json` file of the root project use:
```json
{
    ...,
    &quot;repositories&quot;: [
        {
            &quot;type&quot;: &quot;path&quot;,
            &quot;url&quot;: &quot;../modules/wrux/Core&quot;
        }
    ],
    ...
}
```

Then from the root of the project require your package with: `composer require wrux/Core` and you should see composer acting like if you are downloading an external package, but you are actually using your filesystem as a repository for that package.

